What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Agriculture M2M Market?



Market Analysis and Insights: 

Global Agriculture M2M Market

The agriculture M2M market is expected to be growing at a growth rate of 41.3% in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. The increasing number of networking devices and connections will act as a driving factor for the growth of the agriculture M2M market. This means that the agriculture M2M market value, which was USD 2.5 million in 2020 will climb up to USD 39.72 million by the year 2028.

The word machine to machine (M2M) is utilized to define a technology that allows connected devices to share data or information and achieve various actions without human assistance. An agricultural machine to machine M2M is applied to define irrigation systems, vehicles, and weather stations that are connected to each other utilizing telecom network and core software for the examination and delivery of instructions. Agriculture M2M is a part of the growing internet of things trend, where the devices can be retrieved and controlled over the network.

Upsurge in the demand for the food production, increase in the energy prices and the decrease of the underground water levels are few of the major factors that are further inducing growth of the agriculture M2M market in the forecast period. Furthermore, the loss of farmland because of the fast urbanization and the swift alteration of the agricultural sector concerning the smart farming is further estimated to propel the growth of the agriculture M2M market in the timeline period. Moreover, increase in the awareness amongst farmers to make informed decisions to enhance the yields and rise in the effectiveness and transparency within the agricultural value chain is further projected to supplement the growth of the agriculture M2M market in throughout the forecast period.

On the other hand, increase in the prices of setting up and maintenance services are further anticipated to derail the growth of the agriculture M2M market in the coming years. In addition, mobile operators discovering various prospects to increase their facilities apart from connectivity, focus on the large part of the market, and upsurge the sustainability of their businesses which will further generate lucrative and remunerative growth opportunities for the agriculture M2M market. However, the inadequate network coverage, and the limited understanding of business cases might further challenge the growth of the agriculture M2M market.

